How To Install GNOME On Triaxis
Make sure you are on base with no desktop environment
1 run sudo pacman -S gnome gnome-extra; sudo pacman -S gdm; sudo systemctl enable gdm; sudo systemctl start gdm
2 Login To GNOME
3 Run sudo pacman -S gnome-console
4 Run sudo pacman -S gnome-software gnome-shell-extensions gnome-tweaks gnome-backgrounds
5 Open GNOME Tweaks
6 If You Are New User Who Wants To Switch KDE Plasma To GNOME Go To Appearance Then Cursor Adwaita Icons Adwaita Legacy Applications Adwaita Then Go To System Sound Theme Then Select Default
7 For New KDE Plasma User Who Switched From KDE Plasma To GNOME Go To Windows Then Uncheck Maximize And Minimize Titlebar Buttons
8 For New KDE Plasma User Who Switched From KDE Plasma To GNOME Remove All KDE Plasma Apps With sudo pacman -Rns plasma-meta then sudo pacman -Rns kate
9 Then sudo pacman -Syu
10 Install GNOME Apps
sudo pacman -S nautilus gedit gnome-system-monitor gnome-control-center -y
sudo pacman -S gnome-tweaks gnome-control-center gnome-calculator gnome-disk-utility gnome-screenshot -y
sudo pacman -S gnome-weather gnome-maps gnome-clocks gnome-contacts gnome-photos -y
11 For KDE Plasma User Who Want To Keep Wallpaper You can Use sudo mv and select what wallpaper you want example sudo mv /usr/share/wallpapers/frozenworld-compile-it /usr/share/backgrounds
